= OpenICC project =

OpenICC has two main goals. The first goal is to work out a common set of settings for color savvy applications to share profiles and settings. The second goal is to bring together those developers in areas like printing, display and desktop applications to work together to make color management end to end work for open source applications.

A draft specification hoped be published in 2005.

= Getting involved =

If you are planning to add color management to your software project or you are hardware manufacturer who wishes to extend his clients base by deeping toes into opensource water, we encourage you to join our mailing list. Subscription page is [http://lists.freedesktop.org/mailman/listinfo/openicc just round the corner]. #openicc is now available on irc.freenode.net

